From fd8899b779fa04c47765c5f3f9e7490d36b06a1f Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: radhevrishi <radhev.232@gmail.com>
Date: Fri, 8 May 2026 14:27:11 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 15/17] fix(security): kill leaked FMP key, kill
 NEXT_PUBLIC_BOT_SECRET, rate-limit /api/* via middleware
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

After audit:
1. earnings-analysis client component had FMP_KEY hardcoded as a string
   (visible in browser Sources tab → quota drainable)
2. lib/config.ts shipped BOT_SECRET via NEXT_PUBLIC_* with a hardcoded
   fallback ('mc-bot-2026') → portfolio/watchlist write paths wide open
3. Server routes (estimates, history) had the same FMP_KEY hardcoded as
   a fallback string, leaking via the public GitHub repo
4. No global rate limiting on /api/* — only 3 of 30+ routes had
   per-route rate limits
5. No middleware.ts at all

Changes:

A. NEW /api/earnings/fmp-proxy route
   - Allowlists: earnings-surprises, analyst-estimates, profile,
     income-statement, balance-sheet-statement, cash-flow-statement,
     quote, earnings, price-target-summary, grades, key-metrics-ttm
   - Rate limit: 60 req/min/IP
   - Server-only FMP_KEY env var; no fallback string. Returns 503 when
     env var is missing.
   - 5-minute response cache.

B. earnings-analysis page.tsx — all 9 direct browser-side fetches to
   financialmodelingprep.com replaced with /api/earnings/fmp-proxy
   calls via fmpFetch() / unwrapFmpJson() helpers. The client no longer
   knows the FMP key.

C. lib/config.ts BOT_SECRET fallback removed: `process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_BOT_SECRET ?? ''`
   instead of `?? 'mc-bot-2026'`. Server routes (portfolio, watchlist,
   bot/*) now check both `BOT_SECRET` (truthiness) AND token equality
   so an empty MC_BOT_SECRET env var fails closed instead of accepting
   any empty token.

D. Server routes (api/earnings/estimates, api/earnings/history)
   FMP_KEY fallback string removed.

E. NEW frontend/src/middleware.ts
   Edge middleware applies tiered rate limits to all /api/* routes:
   - 30 req/min/IP for heavy routes (india-screener, india, history,
     edgar, estimates, fmp-proxy, concall/parse, multibagger)
   - 120 req/min/IP for everything else
   X-RateLimit-Limit / X-RateLimit-Remaining / Retry-After headers
   on every response.

F. india-screener route also gets a per-route 30/min rate limit on top
   of the middleware (defense in depth, since the screener scrape is
   the single most expensive endpoint).

POST-DEPLOY ACTION REQUIRED:
After this lands on Vercel, ROTATE the FMP API key on FMP's dashboard.
The previous key is in git history (visible at
github.com/radhevrishi/market-cockpit history) and should be considered
compromised. New key goes in Vercel env vars as FMP_KEY.

If you also want web client portfolio/watchlist writes to work again,
set MC_BOT_SECRET in Vercel env (any random string), and have the
client send it in request bodies — but real per-user auth (next-auth
or similar) is the proper long-term fix.

